post 2: Just want to send a special happy birthday to my wife - my best friend, my advisor, my partner in crime and in love. Your patience, kind heart, focus, intelligence and your resilience in the face of life's obstacles makes me so lucky to be called your husband. To witness and stand by the woman you've grown into is amazing. I look forward to celebrating many more birthdays with you. Happy birthday my love.
matched rules: IF a person indicates a willingness to try new things and participate in a variety of activities, THEN openness is likely High because it demonstrates adaptability and exploration.
matched behaviors: The decoration on the house was amazing. Massive shout out to whoever made the ribs, chicken wings and burgers - 10/10.

post 1: It feels so good to have the gang back together again! we had a lush dinner at Il Michelangelo and won a few games of bowling over at AllStars xoxo we loved reliving the same excitement from when we were young ~ that was 13 years ago! :O <3 P.S. no one noticed that my heel was starting to break...
post 2: my darling, my dearest. I couldn't imagine life without you and your dimpled smiles and cuddles. when life gets tough, you're there for me and me for you. I feel so blessed that we found each other and that we get to share this adventure of life together. You've hit a quarter of a century and here's to many more. I love you, happy birthday! <3
matched rules: IF a person describes reminiscing about past friendships and emphasizes the importance of those experiences without mentioning new activities, THEN openness is likely Low because it indicates a preference for familiar connections over seeking new ones.
matched behaviors: reliving the same excitement from when we were young ~ that was 13 years ago

post 1: What a blast from the past it was last night!   50 years since we all left Morgan and went out into the big wide world.   It was amazing to see some of the old faces, some I barely recognised while with others we went straight back to third year French class!  Awesome to catch up with Brucie, Govie and Tich, but sobering to hear about those who are no longer with us.   Be grateful for every day.
post 2: Woo hoo!  Bill is 70!   How did I come to be married to such an old man???   Thank you for putting up with me for all these years and am looking forward to celebrating with you tonight.  Play your cards right - I might just have a wee surprise for you later on!  In the meantime enjoy your cake, it's your favourite!

post 1: so after an exciting wait - we finally all met up , Parsons meads Class of 1987. It had been a while and now we all had a few more wrinkles and grey hairs. The room was full of laughter and hugs and kisses as we all remembered the school days. we had a laugh and caught up with all the news about our families and planned the next catch up.
post 2: So my darling hubbie, the big day has come - the big 50. Half a century , wow who would have thought it. We have know each other for 33 years of that time, where has it gone. A few more grey hairs and wrinkles between us but we have 2 lovely kids and a great family. Happy Birthday!
